enum Slic3r::GUI::Plater::priv::UpdateBackgroundProcessReturnState
Enumerator
UPDATE_BACKGROUND_PROCESS_RESTART 
UPDATE_BACKGROUND_PROCESS_REFRESH_SCENE 
UPDATE_BACKGROUND_PROCESS_INVALID 
UPDATE_BACKGROUND_PROCESS_FORCE_RESTART 
UPDATE_BACKGROUND_PROCESS_FORCE_EXPORT 
2030 {
2031 // update_background_process() reports, that the Print / SLAPrint was updated in a way,
2032 // that the background process was invalidated and it needs to be re-run.
2033 UPDATE_BACKGROUND_PROCESS_RESTART = 1,
2034 // update_background_process() reports, that the Print / SLAPrint was updated in a way,
2035 // that a scene needs to be refreshed (you should call _3DScene::reload_scene(canvas3Dwidget, false))
2036 UPDATE_BACKGROUND_PROCESS_REFRESH_SCENE = 2,
2037 // update_background_process() reports, that the Print / SLAPrint is invalid, and the error message
2038 // was sent to the status line.
2039 UPDATE_BACKGROUND_PROCESS_INVALID = 4,
2040 // Restart even if the background processing is disabled.
2041 UPDATE_BACKGROUND_PROCESS_FORCE_RESTART = 8,
2042 // Restart for G-code (or SLA zip) export or upload.
2043 UPDATE_BACKGROUND_PROCESS_FORCE_EXPORT = 16,
2044 };

◆ can_fix_through_netfabb()

bool Slic3r::GUI::Plater::priv::can_fix_through_netfabb ( ) const
7151{
7152 std::vector<int> obj_idxs, vol_idxs;
7153 sidebar->obj_list()->get_selection_indexes(obj_idxs, vol_idxs);
7154
7155#if FIX_THROUGH_NETFABB_ALWAYS
7156 // Fixing always.
7157 return ! obj_idxs.empty() || ! vol_idxs.empty();
7158#else // FIX_THROUGH_NETFABB_ALWAYS
7159 // Fixing only if the model is not manifold.
7160 if (vol_idxs.empty()) {
7161 for (auto obj_idx : obj_idxs)
7162 if (model.objects[obj_idx]->get_repaired_errors_count() > 0)
7163 return true;
7164 return false;
7165 }
7166
7167 int obj_idx = obj_idxs.front();
7168 for (auto vol_idx : vol_idxs)
7169 if (model.objects[obj_idx]->get_repaired_errors_count(vol_idx) > 0)
7170 return true;
7171 return false;
7172#endif // FIX_THROUGH_NETFABB_ALWAYS
7173}

◆ can_reload_from_disk()

bool Slic3r::GUI::Plater::priv::can_reload_from_disk ( ) const
6979{
6980 if (sidebar->obj_list()->has_selected_cut_object())
6981 return false;
6982
6983#if ENABLE_RELOAD_FROM_DISK_REWORK
6984 // collect selected reloadable ModelVolumes
6985 std::vector<std::pair<int, int>> selected_volumes = reloadable_volumes(model, get_selection());
6986 // nothing to reload, return
6987 if (selected_volumes.empty())
6988 return false;
6989#else
6990 // struct to hold selected ModelVolumes by their indices
6991 struct SelectedVolume
6992 {
6993 int object_idx;
6994 int volume_idx;
6995
6996 // operators needed by std::algorithms
6997 bool operator < (const SelectedVolume& other) const { return (object_idx < other.object_idx) || ((object_idx == other.object_idx) && (volume_idx < other.volume_idx)); }
6998 bool operator == (const SelectedVolume& other) const { return (object_idx == other.object_idx) && (volume_idx == other.volume_idx); }
6999 };
7000 std::vector<SelectedVolume> selected_volumes;
7001
7002 const Selection& selection = get_selection();
7003
7004 // collects selected ModelVolumes
7005 const std::set<unsigned int>& selected_volumes_idxs = selection.get_volume_idxs();
7006 for (unsigned int idx : selected_volumes_idxs) {
7007 const GLVolume* v = selection.get_volume(idx);
7008 int v_idx = v->volume_idx();
7009 if (v_idx >= 0) {
7010 int o_idx = v->object_idx();
7011 if (0 <= o_idx && o_idx < (int)model.objects.size())
7012 selected_volumes.push_back({ o_idx, v_idx });
7013 }
7014 }
7015#endif // ENABLE_RELOAD_FROM_DISK_REWORK
7016
7017#if ENABLE_RELOAD_FROM_DISK_REWORK
7018 std::sort(selected_volumes.begin(), selected_volumes.end(), [](const std::pair<int, int> &v1, const std::pair<int, int> &v2) {
7019 return (v1.first < v2.first) || (v1.first == v2.first && v1.second < v2.second);
7020 });
7021 selected_volumes.erase(std::unique(selected_volumes.begin(), selected_volumes.end(), [](const std::pair<int, int> &v1, const std::pair<int, int> &v2) {
7022 return (v1.first == v2.first) && (v1.second == v2.second);
7023 }), selected_volumes.end());
7024
7025 // collects paths of files to load
7026 std::vector<fs::path> paths;
7027 for (auto [obj_idx, vol_idx] : selected_volumes) {
7028 paths.push_back(model.objects[obj_idx]->volumes[vol_idx]->source.input_file);
7029 }
7030#else
7031 std::sort(selected_volumes.begin(), selected_volumes.end());
7032 selected_volumes.erase(std::unique(selected_volumes.begin(), selected_volumes.end()), selected_volumes.end());
7033
7034 // collects paths of files to load
7035 std::vector<fs::path> paths;
7036 for (const SelectedVolume& v : selected_volumes) {
7037 const ModelObject* object = model.objects[v.object_idx];
7038 const ModelVolume* volume = object->volumes[v.volume_idx];
7039 if (!volume->source.input_file.empty())
7040 paths.push_back(volume->source.input_file);
7041 else if (!object->input_file.empty() && !volume->name.empty() && !volume->source.is_from_builtin_objects)
7042 paths.push_back(volume->name);
7043 }
7044#endif // ENABLE_RELOAD_FROM_DISK_REWORK
7045 std::sort(paths.begin(), paths.end());
7046 paths.erase(std::unique(paths.begin(), paths.end()), paths.end());
7047
7048 return !paths.empty();
7049}

PlateBBoxData Slic3r::GUI::Plater::priv::generate_first_layer_bbox ( )
6591{
6592 PlateBBoxData bboxdata;
6593 std::vector<BBoxData>& id_bboxes = bboxdata.bbox_objs;
6594 BoundingBoxf bbox_all;
6595 auto print = this->background_process.m_fff_print;
6596 auto curr_plate = this->partplate_list.get_curr_plate();
6597 auto curr_plate_seq = curr_plate->get_real_print_seq();
6598 bboxdata.is_seq_print = (curr_plate_seq == PrintSequence::ByObject);
6599 bboxdata.first_extruder = print->get_tool_ordering().first_extruder();
6600 bboxdata.bed_type = bed_type_to_gcode_string(print->config().curr_bed_type.value);
6601 // get nozzle diameter
6602 auto opt_nozzle_diameters = print->config().option<ConfigOptionFloats>("nozzle_diameter");
6603 if (opt_nozzle_diameters != nullptr)
6604 bboxdata.nozzle_diameter = float(opt_nozzle_diameters->get_at(bboxdata.first_extruder));
6605 //PrintObjectPtrs objects;
6606 //if (this->printer_technology == ptFFF) {
6607 // objects = this->background_process.m_fff_print->objects().vector();
6608 //}
6609 //else {
6610 // objects = this->background_process.m_sla_print->objects();
6611 //}
6612 auto objects = print->objects();
6613 auto orig = this->partplate_list.get_curr_plate()->get_origin();
6614 Vec2d orig2d = { orig[0], orig[1] };
6615
6616 BBoxData data;
6617 for (auto obj : objects)
6618 {
6619 auto bb_scaled = obj->get_first_layer_bbox(data.area, data.layer_height, data.name);
6620 auto bb = unscaled(bb_scaled);
6621 bb.min -= orig2d;
6622 bb.max -= orig2d;
6623 bbox_all.merge(bb);
6624 data.area *= (SCALING_FACTOR * SCALING_FACTOR); // unscale area
6625 data.id = obj->id().id;
6626 data.bbox = { bb.min.x(),bb.min.y(),bb.max.x(),bb.max.y() };
6627 id_bboxes.emplace_back(data);
6628 }
6629
6630 // add wipe tower bounding box
6631 if (print->has_wipe_tower()) {
6632 auto wt_corners = print->first_layer_wipe_tower_corners();
6633 // when loading gcode.3mf, wipe tower info may not be correct
6634 if (!wt_corners.empty()) {
6635 BoundingBox bb_scaled = {wt_corners[0], wt_corners[2]};
6636 auto bb = unscaled(bb_scaled);
6637 bb.min -= orig2d;
6638 bb.max -= orig2d;
6639 bbox_all.merge(bb);
6640 data.name = "wipe_tower";
6641 data.id = partplate_list.get_curr_plate()->get_index() + 1000;
6642 data.bbox = {bb.min.x(), bb.min.y(), bb.max.x(), bb.max.y()};
6643 id_bboxes.emplace_back(data);
6644 }
6645 }
6646
6647 bboxdata.bbox_all = { bbox_all.min.x(),bbox_all.min.y(),bbox_all.max.x(),bbox_all.max.y() };
6648 return bboxdata;
6649}

3771 auto *object = model.add_object(*model_object);
3772 object->sort_volumes(true);
3773 std::string object_name = object->name.empty() ? fs::path(object->input_file).filename().string() : object->name;
3774 obj_idxs.push_back(obj_count++);
3775
3776 if (model_object->instances.empty()) {
3777#ifdef AUTOPLACEMENT_ON_LOAD
3778 object->center_around_origin();
3779 new_instances.emplace_back(object->add_instance());
3780#else /* AUTOPLACEMENT_ON_LOAD */
3781 // if object has no defined position(s) we need to rearrange everything after loading
3782 // need_arrange = true;
3783 // add a default instance and center object around origin
3784 object->center_around_origin(); // also aligns object to Z = 0
3785 ModelInstance* instance = object->add_instance();
3786
3787 //BBS calc transformation
3788 Geometry::Transformation t = instance->get_transformation();
3789 instance->set_offset(Slic3r::to_3d(this->bed.build_volume().bed_center(), -object->origin_translation(2)));
3790#endif /* AUTOPLACEMENT_ON_LOAD */
3791 }
3792
3793 //BBS: when the object is too large, let the user choose whether to scale it down
3794 for (size_t i = 0; i < object->instances.size(); ++i) {
3795 ModelInstance* instance = object->instances[i];
3796 const Vec3d size = object->instance_bounding_box(i).size();
3797 const Vec3d ratio = size.cwiseQuotient(bed_size);
3798 const double max_ratio = std::max(ratio(0), ratio(1));
3799 if (max_ratio > 10000) {
3800 MessageDialog dlg(q, _L("Your object appears to be too large, Do you want to scale it down to fit the heat bed automatically?"), _L("Object too large"),
3801 wxICON_QUESTION | wxYES);
3802 int answer = dlg.ShowModal();
3803 // the size of the object is too big -> this could lead to overflow when moving to clipper coordinates,
3804 // so scale down the mesh
3805 object->scale_mesh_after_creation(1. / max_ratio);
3806 object->origin_translation = Vec3d::Zero();
3807 object->center_around_origin();
3808 scaled_down = true;
3809 break;
3810 }
3811 else if (max_ratio > 10) {
3812 MessageDialog dlg(q, _L("Your object appears to be too large, Do you want to scale it down to fit the heat bed automatically?"), _L("Object too large"),
3813 wxICON_QUESTION | wxYES_NO);
3814 int answer = dlg.ShowModal();
3815 if (answer == wxID_YES) {
3816 instance->set_scaling_factor(instance->get_scaling_factor() / max_ratio);
3817 scaled_down = true;
3818 }
3819 }
3820 }
3821
3822 object->ensure_on_bed(allow_negative_z);
3823 if (!split_object) {
3824 //BBS initial assemble transformation
3825 for (ModelObject* model_object : model.objects) {
3826 //BBS initialize assemble transformation
3827 for (int i = 0; i < model_object->instances.size(); i++) {
3828 if (!model_object->instances[i]->is_assemble_initialized()) {
3829 model_object->instances[i]->set_assemble_transformation(model_object->instances[i]->get_transformation());
3830 }
3831 }
3832 }
3833 }
3834 }
3835
3836#ifdef AUTOPLACEMENT_ON_LOAD
3837#if 0
3838 // FIXME distance should be a config value /////////////////////////////////
3839 auto min_obj_distance = static_cast<coord_t>(6/SCALING_FACTOR);
3840 const auto *bed_shape_opt = config->opt<ConfigOptionPoints>("printable_area");
3841 assert(bed_shape_opt);
3842 auto& bedpoints = bed_shape_opt->values;
3843 Polyline bed; bed.points.reserve(bedpoints.size());
3844 for(auto& v : bedpoints) bed.append(Point::new_scale(v(0), v(1)));
3845
3846 // BBS: get wipe tower of current plate
3847 int cur_plate_idx = partplate_list.get_curr_plate_index();
3848 std::pair<bool, GLCanvas3D::WipeTowerInfo> wti = view3D->get_canvas3d()->get_wipe_tower_info(cur_plate_idx);
3849
3850 arr::find_new_position(model, new_instances, min_obj_distance, bed, wti);
3851
3852 // it remains to move the wipe tower:
3853 view3D->get_canvas3d()->arrange_wipe_tower(wti);
3854#else
3855 // BBS: find an empty cell to put the copied object
3856 for (auto& instance : new_instances) {
3857 auto offset = instance->get_offset();
3858 auto start_point = this->bed.build_volume().bounding_volume2d().center();
3859 bool plate_empty = partplate_list.get_curr_plate()->empty();
3860 Vec3d displacement;
3861 if (plate_empty)
3862 displacement = {start_point(0), start_point(1), offset(2)};
3863 else {
3864 auto empty_cell = wxGetApp().plater()->canvas3D()->get_nearest_empty_cell({start_point(0), start_point(1)});
3865 displacement = {empty_cell.x(), empty_cell.y(), offset(2)};
3866 }
3867 instance->set_offset(displacement);
3868 }
3869#endif
3870
3871#endif /* AUTOPLACEMENT_ON_LOAD */
3872
3873 //BBS: remove the auto scaled_down logic when load models
3874 //if (scaled_down) {
3875 // GUI::show_info(q,
3876 // _L("Your object appears to be too large, so it was automatically scaled down to fit your print bed."),
3877 // _L("Object too large?"));
3878 //}
3879
3880 notification_manager->close_notification_of_type(NotificationType::UpdatedItemsInfo);
3881 wxGetApp().obj_list()->add_objects_to_list(obj_idxs);
3882
3883 update();
3884 // Update InfoItems in ObjectList after update() to use of a correct value of the GLCanvas3D::is_sinking(),
3885 // which is updated after a view3D->reload_scene(false, flags & (unsigned int)UpdateParams::FORCE_FULL_SCREEN_REFRESH) call
3886 for (const size_t idx : obj_idxs)
3887 wxGetApp().obj_list()->update_info_items(idx);
3888
3889 object_list_changed();
3890
3891 this->schedule_background_process();
3892
3893 return obj_idxs;
3894}

◆ on_right_click()

void Slic3r::GUI::Plater::priv::on_right_click ( RBtnEvent &  evt)
6461{

6463
6464 wxMenu* menu = nullptr;
6465
6466 if (obj_idx == -1) { // no one or several object are selected

◆ on_slicing_update()

void Slic3r::GUI::Plater::priv::on_slicing_update ( SlicingStatusEvent &  evt)
5727{
5728 BOOST_LOG_TRIVIAL(debug) << __FUNCTION__ << boost::format(": event_type %1%, percent %2%, text %3%") % evt.GetEventType() % evt.status.percent % evt.status.text;
5729 //BBS: add slice project logic
5730 std::string title_text = _u8L("Slicing");
5731 evt.status.text = title_text + evt.status.text;
5732 if (evt.status.percent >= 0) {
5733 if (m_ui_jobs.is_any_running()) {
5734 // Avoid a race condition
5735 return;
5736 }
5737
5738 notification_manager->set_slicing_progress_percentage(evt.status.text, (float)evt.status.percent / 100.0f);
5739
5740 // update slicing percent
5741 PartPlateList& plate_list = wxGetApp().plater()->get_partplate_list();
5742 //slicing parallel, only update if percent is greater than before
5743 if (evt.status.percent > plate_list.get_curr_plate()->get_slicing_percent())
5744 plate_list.get_curr_plate()->update_slicing_percent(evt.status.percent);
5745 }
5746
5747 if (evt.status.flags & (PrintBase::SlicingStatus::RELOAD_SCENE | PrintBase::SlicingStatus::RELOAD_SLA_SUPPORT_POINTS)) {
5748 switch (this->printer_technology) {
5749 case ptFFF:
5750 //BBS: add slice project logic, only display shells at the beginning
5751 if (!m_slice_all || (m_cur_slice_plate == (partplate_list.get_plate_count() - 1)))
5752 //this->update_fff_scene();
5753 this->update_fff_scene_only_shells();
5754 break;
5755 case ptSLA:
5756 // If RELOAD_SLA_SUPPORT_POINTS, then the SLA gizmo is updated (reload_scene calls update_gizmos_data)
5757 if (view3D->is_dragging())
5758 delayed_scene_refresh = true;
5759 else
5760 this->update_sla_scene();
5761 break;
5762 default: break;
5763 }
5764 } else if (evt.status.flags & PrintBase::SlicingStatus::RELOAD_SLA_PREVIEW) {
5765 // Update the SLA preview. Only called if not RELOAD_SLA_SUPPORT_POINTS, as the block above will refresh the preview anyways.
5766 this->preview->reload_print();
5767 }
5768
5769 if (evt.status.flags & (PrintBase::SlicingStatus::UPDATE_PRINT_STEP_WARNINGS | PrintBase::SlicingStatus::UPDATE_PRINT_OBJECT_STEP_WARNINGS)) {
5770 // Update notification center with warnings of object_id and its warning_step.
5771 ObjectID object_id = evt.status.warning_object_id;
5772 int warning_step = evt.status.warning_step;
5773 PrintStateBase::StateWithWarnings state;
5774 ModelObject const * model_object = nullptr;
5775
5776 //BBS: add partplate related logic, use the print in background process
5777 if (evt.status.flags & PrintBase::SlicingStatus::UPDATE_PRINT_STEP_WARNINGS) {
5778 state = this->printer_technology == ptFFF ?
5779 this->background_process.m_fff_print->step_state_with_warnings(static_cast<PrintStep>(warning_step)) :
5780 this->background_process.m_sla_print->step_state_with_warnings(static_cast<SLAPrintStep>(warning_step));
5781 } else if (this->printer_technology == ptFFF) {
5782 const PrintObject *print_object = this->background_process.m_fff_print->get_object(object_id);
5783 if (print_object) {
5784 state = print_object->step_state_with_warnings(static_cast<PrintObjectStep>(warning_step));
5785 model_object = print_object->model_object();
5786 }
5787 } else {
5788 const SLAPrintObject *print_object = this->background_process.m_sla_print->get_object(object_id);
5789 if (print_object) {
5790 state = print_object->step_state_with_warnings(static_cast<SLAPrintObjectStep>(warning_step));
5791 model_object = print_object->model_object();
5792 }
5793 }
5794 // Now process state.warnings.
5795 for (auto const& warning : state.warnings) {
5796 if (warning.current) {
5797 notification_manager->push_slicing_warning_notification(warning.message, false, model_object, object_id, warning_step, warning.message_id);
5798 add_warning(warning, object_id.id);
5799 }
5800 }
5801 }
5802 BOOST_LOG_TRIVIAL(debug) << __FUNCTION__ << boost::format("exit.");
5803}

5278 for (size_t i = 0; i < replace_paths.size(); ++i) {
5279 const auto& path = replace_paths[i].string();
5280 for (const SelectedVolume& sel_v : selected_volumes) {
5281 ModelObject* old_model_object = model.objects[sel_v.object_idx];
5282 ModelVolume* old_volume = old_model_object->volumes[sel_v.volume_idx];
5283 bool has_source = !old_volume->source.input_file.empty() && boost::algorithm::iequals(fs::path(old_volume->source.input_file).filename().string(), fs::path(path).filename().string());
5284 if (!replace_volume_with_stl(sel_v.object_idx, sel_v.volume_idx, path, "")) {
5285 fail_list.push_back(from_u8(has_source ? old_volume->source.input_file : old_volume->name));
5286 }
5287 }
5288 }
5289#endif // ENABLE_RELOAD_FROM_DISK_REWORK
5290
5291 if (!fail_list.empty()) {
5292 wxString message = _devL("Unable to reload:") + "\n";
5293 for (const wxString& s : fail_list) {
5294 message += s + "\n";
5295 }
5296 MessageDialog dlg(q, message, _devL("Error during reload"), wxOK | wxOK_DEFAULT | wxICON_WARNING);
5297 dlg.ShowModal();
5298 }
5299
5300 // update 3D scene
5301 update();
5302
5303 // new GLVolumes have been created at this point, so update their printable state
5304 for (size_t i = 0; i < model.objects.size(); ++i) {
5305 view3D->get_canvas3d()->update_instance_printable_state_for_object(i);
5306 }
5307}

bool Slic3r::GUI::Plater::priv::replace_volume_with_stl ( int  object_idx,

)
4768{
4769 const std::string path = new_path.string();
4770 wxBusyCursor wait;
4771 wxBusyInfo info(_devL("Replace from:") + " " + from_u8(path), q->get_current_canvas3D()->get_wxglcanvas());
4772
4773 Model new_model;
4774 try {
4775 new_model = Model::read_from_file(path, nullptr, nullptr, LoadStrategy::AddDefaultInstances);
4776 for (ModelObject* model_object : new_model.objects) {
4777 model_object->center_around_origin();
4778 model_object->ensure_on_bed();
4779 }
4780 }
4781 catch (std::exception&) {
4782 // error while loading
4783 return false;
4784 }
4785
4786 if (new_model.objects.size() > 1 || new_model.objects.front()->volumes.size() > 1) {
4787 MessageDialog dlg(q, _devL("Unable to replace with more than one volume"), _devL("Error during replace"), wxOK | wxOK_DEFAULT | wxICON_WARNING);
4788 dlg.ShowModal();
4789 return false;
4790 }
4791
4792 if (!snapshot.empty())
4793 q->take_snapshot(snapshot);
4794
4795 ModelObject* old_model_object = model.objects[object_idx];
4796 ModelVolume* old_volume = old_model_object->volumes[volume_idx];
4797
4798 bool sinking = old_model_object->bounding_box().min.z() < SINKING_Z_THRESHOLD;
4799
4800 ModelObject* new_model_object = new_model.objects.front();
4801 old_model_object->add_volume(*new_model_object->volumes.front());
4802 ModelVolume* new_volume = old_model_object->volumes.back();
4803 new_volume->set_new_unique_id();
4804 new_volume->config.apply(old_volume->config);
4805 new_volume->set_type(old_volume->type());
4806 new_volume->set_material_id(old_volume->material_id());
4807 new_volume->set_transformation(old_volume->get_transformation());
4808 new_volume->translate(new_volume->get_transformation().get_matrix(true) * (new_volume->source.mesh_offset - old_volume->source.mesh_offset));
4809 assert(!old_volume->source.is_converted_from_inches || !old_volume->source.is_converted_from_meters);
4810 if (old_volume->source.is_converted_from_inches)
4811 new_volume->convert_from_imperial_units();
4812 else if (old_volume->source.is_converted_from_meters)
4813 new_volume->convert_from_meters();
4814 new_volume->supported_facets.assign(old_volume->supported_facets);
4815 new_volume->seam_facets.assign(old_volume->seam_facets);
4816 new_volume->mmu_segmentation_facets.assign(old_volume->mmu_segmentation_facets);
4817 std::swap(old_model_object->volumes[volume_idx], old_model_object->volumes.back());
4818 old_model_object->delete_volume(old_model_object->volumes.size() - 1);
4819 if (!sinking)
4820 old_model_object->ensure_on_bed();
4821 old_model_object->sort_volumes(true);
4822
4823 // if object has just one volume, rename object too
4824 if (old_model_object->volumes.size() == 1)
4825 old_model_object->name = old_model_object->volumes.front()->name;
4826
4827 // update new name in ObjectList
4828 sidebar->obj_list()->update_name_in_list(object_idx, volume_idx);
4829
4830 sla::reproject_points_and_holes(old_model_object);
4831
4832 return true;
4833}

4608{

4610 // Avoid a race condition

4624 on_slicing_began();

4450 //this->background_process.get_current_gcode_result()->reset();
4451 // Reset preview canvases. If the print has been invalidated, the preview canvases will be cleared.
4452 // Otherwise they will be just refreshed.
4453 if (preview != nullptr) {
4454 // If the preview is not visible, the following line just invalidates the preview,
4455 // but the G-code paths or SLA preview are calculated first once the preview is made visible.
4456 reset_gcode_toolpaths();
4457 preview->reload_print();
4458 }
4459 // In FDM mode, we need to reload the 3D scene because of the wipe tower preview box.
4460 // In SLA mode, we need to reload the 3D scene every time to show the support structures.
4461 if (printer_technology == ptSLA || (printer_technology == ptFFF && config->opt_bool("enable_prime_tower")))
4462 return_state |= UPDATE_BACKGROUND_PROCESS_REFRESH_SCENE;
4463
4464 notification_manager->set_slicing_progress_hidden();
4465 }
4466
4467 if ((invalidated != Print::APPLY_STATUS_UNCHANGED || force_validation) && ! background_process.empty()) {
4468 // The delayed error message is no more valid.
4469 delayed_error_message.clear();
4470 // The state of the Print changed, and it is non-zero. Let's validate it and give the user feedback on errors.
4471
4472 //BBS: add is_warning logic
4473 StringObjectException warning;
4474 //BBS: refine seq-print logic
4475 Polygons polygons;
4476 std::vector<std::pair<Polygon, float>> height_polygons;
4477 StringObjectException err = background_process.validate(&warning, &polygons, &height_polygons);
4478 // update string by type
4479 q->post_process_string_object_exception(err);
4480 BOOST_LOG_TRIVIAL(info) << __FUNCTION__ << boost::format(": validate err=%1%, warning=%2%")%err.string%warning.string;
4481
4482 if (err.string.empty()) {
4483 this->partplate_list.get_curr_plate()->update_apply_result_invalid(false);
4484 notification_manager->set_all_slicing_errors_gray(true);
4485 notification_manager->close_notification_of_type(NotificationType::ValidateError);
4486 if (invalidated != Print::APPLY_STATUS_UNCHANGED && background_processing_enabled())
4487 return_state |= UPDATE_BACKGROUND_PROCESS_RESTART;
4488
4489 // Pass a warning from validation and either show a notification,
4490 // or hide the old one.
4491 process_validation_warning(warning);
4492 if (printer_technology == ptFFF) {
4493 view3D->get_canvas3d()->reset_sequential_print_clearance();
4494 view3D->get_canvas3d()->set_as_dirty();
4495 view3D->get_canvas3d()->request_extra_frame();
4496 }
4497 }
4498 else {
4499 this->partplate_list.get_curr_plate()->update_apply_result_invalid(true);
4500 // The print is not valid.
4501 // Show error as notification.
4502 notification_manager->push_validate_error_notification(err);
4503 //also update the warnings
4504 process_validation_warning(warning);
4505 return_state |= UPDATE_BACKGROUND_PROCESS_INVALID;
4506 if (printer_technology == ptFFF) {
4507 const Print* print = background_process.fff_print();
4508 //Polygons polygons;
4509 //if (print->config().print_sequence == PrintSequence::ByObject)
4510 // Print::sequential_print_clearance_valid(*print, &polygons);
4511 view3D->get_canvas3d()->set_sequential_print_clearance_visible(true);
4512 view3D->get_canvas3d()->set_sequential_print_clearance_render_fill(true);
4513 view3D->get_canvas3d()->set_sequential_print_clearance_polygons(polygons, height_polygons);
4514 }
4515 }
4516 }
4517 else if (! this->delayed_error_message.empty()) {
4518 // Reusing the old state.
4519 return_state |= UPDATE_BACKGROUND_PROCESS_INVALID;
4520 }
4521
4522 //actualizate warnings
4523 if (invalidated != Print::APPLY_STATUS_UNCHANGED || background_process.empty()) {
4524 if (background_process.empty())
4525 process_validation_warning({});
4526 actualize_slicing_warnings(*this->background_process.current_print());
4527 actualize_object_warnings(*this->background_process.current_print());
4528 show_warning_dialog = false;
4529 process_completed_with_error = -1;
4530 }
4531
4532 if (invalidated != Print::APPLY_STATUS_UNCHANGED && was_running && ! this->background_process.running() &&
4533 (return_state & UPDATE_BACKGROUND_PROCESS_RESTART) == 0) {
4534 // The background processing was killed and it will not be restarted.
4535 // Post the "canceled" callback message, so that it will be processed after any possible pending status bar update messages.
4536 SlicingProcessCompletedEvent evt(EVT_PROCESS_COMPLETED, 0,
4537 SlicingProcessCompletedEvent::Cancelled, nullptr);
4538 BOOST_LOG_TRIVIAL(info) << __FUNCTION__ << boost::format(" %1%, post an EVT_PROCESS_COMPLETED to main, status %2%")%__LINE__ %evt.status();
4539 wxQueueEvent(q, evt.Clone());
4540 }
4541
4542 if ((return_state & UPDATE_BACKGROUND_PROCESS_INVALID) != 0)
4543 {
4544 // Validation of the background data failed.
4545 //BBS: add slice&&print status update logic
4546 this->main_frame->update_slice_print_status(MainFrame::eEventSliceUpdate, false);
4547
4548 process_completed_with_error = partplate_list.get_curr_plate_index();
4549 BOOST_LOG_TRIVIAL(info) << __FUNCTION__ << boost::format(", Line %1%: set to process_completed_with_error, return_state=%2%")%__LINE__%return_state;
4550 }
4551 else
4552 {
4553 // Background data is valid.
4554 if ((return_state & UPDATE_BACKGROUND_PROCESS_RESTART) != 0 ||
4555 (return_state & UPDATE_BACKGROUND_PROCESS_REFRESH_SCENE) != 0 )
4556 notification_manager->set_slicing_progress_hidden();
4557
4558 //BBS: add slice&&print status update logic
4559 BOOST_LOG_TRIVIAL(info) << __FUNCTION__ << boost::format(", Line %1%: background data valid, return_state=%2%")%__LINE__%return_state;
4560 PartPlate* cur_plate = background_process.get_current_plate();
4561 if (background_process.finished() && cur_plate && cur_plate->is_slice_result_valid())
4562 {
4563 //ready_to_slice = false;
4564 this->main_frame->update_slice_print_status(MainFrame::eEventSliceUpdate, false);
4565 }
4566 else if (!background_process.empty() &&
4567 !background_process.running()) /* Do not update buttons if background process is running
4568 * This condition is important for SLA mode especially,
4569 * when this function is called several times during calculations
4570 * */
4571 {
4572 if (cur_plate->can_slice()) {
4573 //ready_to_slice = true;
4574 this->main_frame->update_slice_print_status(MainFrame::eEventSliceUpdate, true);
4575 process_completed_with_error = -1;
4576 }
4577 else {
4578 //ready_to_slice = false;
4579 this->main_frame->update_slice_print_status(MainFrame::eEventSliceUpdate, false);
4580 process_completed_with_error = partplate_list.get_curr_plate_index();
4581 }
4582 }
4583#if 0
4584 //sidebar->set_btn_label(ActionButtonType::abExport, _(label_btn_export));
4585 //sidebar->set_btn_label(ActionButtonType::abSendGCode, _(label_btn_send));
4586
4587 //const wxString slice_string = background_process.running() && wxGetApp().get_mode() == comSimple ?
4588 // _L("Slicing") + dots : _L("Slice now");
4589 //sidebar->set_btn_label(ActionButtonType::abReslice, slice_string);
4590
4591 //if (background_process.finished())
4592 // show_action_buttons(false);
4593 //else if (!background_process.empty() &&
4594 // !background_process.running()) /* Do not update buttons if background process is running
4595 // * This condition is important for SLA mode especially,
4596 // * when this function is called several times during calculations
4597 // * */
4598 // show_action_buttons(true);
4599#endif
4600 }
4601
4602 BOOST_LOG_TRIVIAL(info) << __FUNCTION__ << boost::format(", Line %1%: exit, return_state=%2%")%__LINE__%return_state;
4603 return return_state;
4604}
